headline: Trouble in Vegas? Caesars Entertainment Stock Tumbles on Earnings.
summary: Shares of  Caesars Entertainment  tumbled Wednesday after the casino operator reported disappointing quarterly earnings, driven in part by weak results in Las Vegas.  Caesars is on pace for its fifth annual loss in six years.  While revenue in regional casinos grew, Las Vegas revenue—it accounts for about one-third of Caesars’ business—dropped 9.8% from a year ago.

headline: Baron Real Estate Income Fund Q3 2025 Top Contributors And Detractors
summary: In Q3, Welltower shares, operator of senior housing, life science, and medical office real estate properties, continued to significantly outperform both the REIT and broader equity indices.

headline: The U.A.E.’s First Legal Casino: Wynn Resorts’ Big Bet
summary: Wynn Resorts is building a $5.1 billion resort that will be the U.A.E.'s first-ever casino. But some experts question if the bet will pay off in a conservative region.
